  📝 Retrieved Answer:
  ----------------------------------------------------------
  The ACID properties of transactions are Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, and Durability. These properties ensure that transactions are processed reliably and consistently, even in the presence of errors or failures. Atomicity ensures that transactions are processed as a single unit of work, with no partial or partial failure. Consistency ensures that transactions maintain the integrity of the database, with no data loss or corruption. Isolation ensures that transactions are processed independently of each other, with no interference or conflict. Durability ensures that transactions are persisted to disk, even in the event of a system failure. These properties are essential for maintaining the reliability and consistency of database systems.
  ----------------------------------------------------------

